Senior Investment Professionals

Andrew J.M. SpokesManaging PartnerSan FranciscoMr. Spokes is the Managing Partner of Farallon. Before joining us in 1997, Mr. Spokes worked in the investment banking division of Goldman Sachs for ten years, most of which time he spent in Europe and Asia. At the time of his departure Mr. Spokes was an Executive Director and Head of Corporate Finance for Goldman Sachs (Asia). Mr. Spokes graduated with a B.A./M.A. in Chemistry from Oxford University.

Lars BaneManaging MemberLondonMr. Bane joined us in 2002, and is a Managing Member of Farallon Capital Europe LLP. Before joining, from 2000-2002, Mr. Bane was head of special situations equity sales at Enskilda Securities in London. Before joining Enskilda, he had a similar role at Nordic Partners in New York and Stockholm. Mr. Bane graduated with a master’s in Finance from Stockholm School of Economics.

Paul CaldwellManaging MemberTokyoMr. Caldwell joined us in 2007 and is Member Executor of the Representative Member of Farallon Capital Japan LLC. Prior to joining, Mr. Caldwell served as an Executive Director at Goldman Sachs’ European Special Situations Group (ESSG). Before joining ESSG, Mr. Caldwell worked for Goldman Sachs’ Whitehall Street Real Estate Funds in Tokyo. Mr. Caldwell graduated summa cum laude from Princeton University with a B.A. in Public Policy.

Philip D. DreyfussManaging MemberSan Francisco (Arbitrage)Mr. Dreyfuss joined us in 2011. Previously, Mr. Dreyfuss was an associate at Bain Capital Partners where he was responsible for evaluating and executing private equity investments in a variety of sectors. Prior to Bain Capital, Mr. Dreyfuss was a management consultant at the Boston Consulting Group where he focused on the healthcare industry. Mr. Dreyfuss graduated summa cum laude from Harvard College where he received an A.M. in Chemistry and an A.B. in Chemistry and Physics, and was elected to Phi Beta Kappa. Mr. Dreyfuss received an M.B.A. with high distinction from Harvard Business School, where he was a Baker Scholar.

Richard B. FriedManaging MemberSan Francisco (Real Estate)Mr. Fried joined us in 1995. Before joining, Mr. Fried worked for Security Capital Industrial Trust, a real estate investment trust specializing in industrial properties. At the time of his departure from Security Capital, he was a Vice President in the acquisitions department. From 1990 to 1993, Mr. Fried was an associate in capital markets at JMB Institutional Realty Corporation. Mr. Fried graduated cum laude with a B.S. in Economics and a B.A. in History from the University of Pennsylvania.

Nicolas GiauqueManaging MemberLondonMr. Giauque joined us in 1998, and is a Managing Member of Farallon Capital Europe LLP. Prior to joining, Mr. Giauque worked in the investment banking and asset management divisions of Goldman Sachs for four years in Hong Kong and Singapore. Mr. Giauque graduated with a master of Management from Hautes Etudes Commerciales.

Daniel GoldbergPartnerSão PauloMr. Goldberg joined us in 2011 and is the Managing Partner of Farallon Latin America Investimentos Ltda. Prior to joining, Mr. Goldberg served as the President of Morgan Stanley in Brazil. Prior to that, he headed Brazil’s antitrust and consumer protection agency as Brazil’s Secretary of Economic Law in its Ministry of Justice. Mr. Goldberg received a law degree and a doctorate degree from University of São Paulo. In addition, he received a Master of Laws from Harvard Law School.

Ashish GuptaPartnerSingaporeMr. Gupta joined us in 2007 and is a Managing Director at Farallon Capital Asia Pte. Ltd. Prior to joining, Mr. Gupta was an associate in the investment banking division of Goldman Sachs in Singapore, where he focused on mergers & acquisitions and capital markets assignments for companies in Asia. Mr. Gupta graduated with a B. Com. (Hons) from University of Delhi. He obtained his post graduate diploma in management from the Indian Institute of Management, Ahmedabad.

David T. KimManaging MemberSan Francisco (Equities)Mr. Kim joined us in 2005. Prior to joining, Mr. Kim was a senior associate at Francisco Partners where he was responsible for evaluating and executing on private equity, technology-focused investments. He has also worked in various roles at Bain Capital Partners, Eastern Advisors, and Bain & Company in previous years. Mr. Kim received an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School, where he was elected Baker Scholar, and an A.B. in Economics with high distinction from Stanford University.

Michael G. LinnManaging MemberSan Francisco (Credit)Mr. Linn joined us in 2002. Prior to joining, Mr. Linn worked as an equity derivatives trader at Bank of America, focused on U.S. single stock volatility trading. Prior to Bank of America, Mr. Linn worked at J.P. Morgan from 1998 to 1999 trading interest rate products. Mr. Linn graduated magna cum laude from the University of Pennsylvania with a B.A. in Economics.

Ravi K. PaidipatyManaging MemberSan Francisco (Equities)Mr. Paidipaty rejoined us in 2008, having been a summer analyst in 2007. Previously, Mr. Paidipaty worked as a private equity associate at Thomas H. Lee Partners, L.P. and as an investment banking analyst at Morgan Stanley. Mr. Paidipaty graduated with Distinction from Yale College with a B.A. in Ethics, Politics & Economics and received his M.B.A. from Harvard Business School.

Rajiv A. PatelManaging MemberSan Francisco (Credit)Mr. Patel joined us in 1997. Prior to joining, Mr. Patel worked at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette as an investment banker in the project finance department. Mr. Patel received an M.B.A. from Stanford Graduate School of Business and graduated from Cornell University as a Merrill Presidential Scholar with a B.S. in Operations Research and Industrial Engineering.

William S. SeyboldManaging MemberSan Francisco (Equities)Mr. Seybold joined us in 2001. Mr. Seybold graduated from Harvard College magna cum laude with an A.B. in Latin American History and Literature.

Dr. Thomas G. Roberts Jr.Managing MemberSan Francisco (Arbitrage)Dr. Roberts joined us in 2005. Prior to joining us, Dr. Roberts was an attending oncologist at Massachusetts General Hospital, an Instructor of Medicine at the Harvard Medical School, and a Visiting Scientist at Massachusetts Institute of Technology. He maintains an active medical license. Dr. Roberts obtained two baccalaureate degrees (summa cum laude) from the University of Pennsylvania, including a B.S. from the Wharton School of Business (elected Phi Beta Kappa junior year). He obtained his medical degree from Harvard Medical School. Dr. Roberts performed his internal medicine training at the Massachusetts General Hospital and his medical oncology training through the Dana-Farber/Partners Cancer Care Oncology Fellowship Program.

John R. WarrenManaging MemberSan Francisco (Equities)Mr. Warren joined us in 2004. Prior to joining, Mr. Warren was an associate at Hellman & Friedman, focusing on equity investments in a variety of sectors. Prior to Hellman & Friedman, Mr. Warren worked as an analyst at Morgan Stanley in the Mergers, Acquisitions & Restructurings Department, where he focused on the media and telecommunications sectors. Mr. Warren graduated magna cum laude from Harvard College with an A.B. in Economics and earned his M.B.A. from Harvard Business School.

Nancy B.Y. WuPartnerHong KongMs. Wu joined us in 2005 and is a Managing Director of Farallon Capital Asia (HK) Limited. Ms. Wu previously worked as a portfolio manager at Goldman Sachs’ internal hedge fund group in Hong Kong, where she was responsible for investing in event driven and value opportunities in non-Japan Asia. Prior to joining Goldman Sachs, Ms. Wu was an analyst in the investment banking division of Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette in both New York and Hong Kong. Ms. Wu graduated with a B.S. in Finance from Massachusetts Institute of Technology where she was elected Phi Beta Kappa.

G. Raymond Zage IIIPartnerSingaporeMr. Zage joined us in 2000 and is Chief Executive Officer of Farallon Capital Asia Pte. Ltd. Prior to joining, Mr. Zage was a Vice President in the investment banking division of Goldman Sachs in Singapore, where he was responsible for working on mergers & acquisitions and corporate finance assignments for companies throughout Asia. Prior to moving to Singapore, Mr. Zage worked in the financial institutions group at Goldman Sachs in both New York and Los Angeles, where he focused on bank mergers and acquisitions. Mr. Zage graduated with a B.S. in Accounting and Finance from the University of Illinois at Urbana Champaign.



Vikram BagariaManaging DirectorSingaporeMr. Bagaria joined us in 2003 and is a Managing Director at Farallon Capital Asia Pte. Ltd. Previously, Mr. Bagaria was a portfolio manager at Onyx Capital in New York, where he was responsible for investing in event driven and capital structure arbitrage opportunities in Europe and Asia. Prior to Onyx, Mr. Bagaria worked for Goldman Sachs in the international equity arbitrage group in New York. Mr. Bagaria was also an analyst in the investment banking division of Goldman Sachs in Singapore, where he worked on mergers & acquisitions and corporate finance assignments for companies throughout Asia. Mr. Bagaria graduated with a B.S. in Economics from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and a M.S. in Accounting and Finance from the London School of Economics and Political Science.

